---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import pricing from '../data/pricing.json';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
import CookieConsent from '../components/CookieConsent.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Rapid Receptionist — The Rapid Response AI Receptionist for UK Construction Trades"
  description="Why we built an AI receptionist exclusively for UK construction trades. 46 trades. 8 channels. One mission: make sure your customers never hear voicemail."
  canonicalUrl="/about/"
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section about-hero" id="about-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge badge--accent">About Us</span>
      <h1>We Built Rapid Receptionist Because <span class="text-accent">Construction Trades Deserve Better</span> Than Voicemail.</h1>
      <p class="about-hero__sub">Every day, skilled contractors across the UK lose work — not because they lack ability, but because their phone rang while their hands were full. Rapid Receptionist exists to close that gap.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Origin Story -->
  <section class="section section--alt" id="origin">
    <div class="container about-content">
      <div class="about-block">
        <h2>The Problem That Triggered Everything</h2>
        <p>The UK construction industry employs over 2.4 million people, and the vast majority of them work with their hands. Plasterers with trowels. Electricians with wire strippers. Roofers with nail guns. Plumbing contractors under sinks. Bricklayers building garden walls in the rain.</p>
        <p>None of them can answer a phone call while they're mid-task. And yet, every day, potential customers ring, hear voicemail, and immediately dial the next contractor on Google. Research consistently shows that 85% of callers who reach voicemail will never ring back. The job is gone in under thirty seconds.</p>
        <p>We spoke with dozens of UK construction businesses — sole traders, small firms, specialist subcontractors — and heard the same frustration repeated: "I'm good at my trade, but I keep losing work because I can't get to the phone." Not because they were lazy or unprofessional. Because they were doing their actual job.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-block">
        <h2>Why Generic Solutions Didn't Work</h2>
        <p>Virtual receptionist services already existed when we started. We examined them all. The fundamental problem was that none of them understood construction.</p>
        <p>A generic answering service doesn't know the difference between a skim coat and a full re-plaster. It can't tell whether a caller describing a damp patch needs a damp proofer, a roofer, or a drainage contractor. It doesn't understand that a gas smell needs escalating immediately while a quote for a boiler swap can wait until Monday.</p>
        <p>So we built something purpose-built for 46 UK construction trades. An AI receptionist trained on trade-specific vocabulary, urgency signals, and job types — from domestic bathroom refits to commercial fit-outs to multi-plot new builds. One that knows what questions to ask, what constitutes an emergency, and what details you need to price a job before you call them back.</p>
        <p>Then we expanded beyond phone calls. Modern customers don't just ring — they WhatsApp, they message on Facebook, they fill in website contact forms, they DM on Instagram. Construction businesses were losing leads across every one of those channels, so we covered all eight of them.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-block">
        <h2>What Drives Every Decision We Make</h2>
        <p>Construction trades keep the country built, heated, waterproofed, wired, and standing. Plasterers, bricklayers, groundworkers, joiners, tilers, roofers, electricians, plumbers — every one of them provides an essential service. They deserve technology that respects their work and helps them grow, not software designed for tech companies and repackaged with a hard-hat logo.</p>
        <p>Every decision at Rapid Receptionist comes back to a single test: does this help a construction business respond faster and win more work? If it does, we build it. If it doesn't, we leave it alone. No feature bloat, no enterprise pricing designed for corporate switchboards, no complexity that requires a training course to understand.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-block">
        <h2>How We Price — and Why</h2>
    <p>We charge £{pricing.tiers.core.price} a month for AI phone answering and website chat — the two channels where construction businesses lose the most leads. Additional channels cost £{pricing.addOn.price}/month each.</p>
        <p>These numbers are deliberate. A single missed enquiry from a homeowner wanting their kitchen re-plastered is worth £400-£800. One commercial tiling contract can be worth £5,000+. The maths is straightforward: if Rapid Receptionist captures one lead you would have otherwise missed, it has paid for itself multiple times over.</p>
        <p>We back everything with a 30-day money-back guarantee — monthly fee and setup fee, fully refunded. If it doesn't deliver results for your trade, you get every penny back.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <section class="section" id="values">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What We <span class="text-accent">Stand For</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="values-grid">
        <div class="value-card fade-in">
          <span class="value-card__icon">🏗️</span>
          <h3>Construction-First Design</h3>
          <p>Every AI response, every channel integration, every configuration option is designed specifically for construction trades. This isn't a generic receptionist service with a construction theme bolt-ed on. It's engineered from the ground up for the way contractors, specialists, and subcontractors actually operate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card fade-in">
          <span class="value-card__icon">👷</span>
          <h3>Honest Pricing</h3>
          <p>One price on the website. Same price on the invoice. No hidden fees, no per-minute charges that inflate your bill, no "premium" tier that locks essential features behind a paywall. What you see is exactly what you pay, every single month.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card fade-in">
          <span class="value-card__icon">🤝</span>
          <h3>No Lock-In</h3>
          <p>No contracts. No minimum terms. No cancellation hoops. Cancel any time with a single message and it takes effect at the end of your billing cycle. We earn your business every month by being good at what we do, not by making it difficult to walk away.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card fade-in">
          <span class="value-card__icon">🇬🇧</span>
          <h3>Built for UK Construction</h3>
          <p>UK pricing in pounds. UK English. UK-specific building terminology, regulations, and trade structures. UK emergency escalation protocols. This service is designed for construction businesses operating in the United Kingdom — not an American product with a UK flag stuck on the homepage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    headline="Respond First. Win the Job."
    subhead=`Join the UK construction trades who never miss a lead. £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month, 30-day money-back guarantee, no contracts.`
  />

  <CookieConsent />

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-16));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-2xl), 4vw, var(--text-4xl));
    font-weight: var(--font-extrabold);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-4) auto var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-hero__sub {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .about-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-block {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about-block:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-block h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-bold);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-block p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Values Grid */
  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .value-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-base);
  }

  .value-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-border-accent);
  }

  .value-card__icon {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .value-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
